oc:kn_0921a7c1 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building balancing sections in financial models" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When two sections must balance (Sources=Uses, Assets=Liabilities), identify one item as the 'plug' and calculate it as the difference rather than forcing both independently." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The plug approach guarantees the section balances by construction rather than relying on two independent calculations to coincidentally match." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_156616e4 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Template analysis phase before any formula writing" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Map structure — identify sections and relationships. 2. Understand timeline — periods, closing/pro forma columns. 3. Identify input vs formula cells via color/borders. 4. Read row labels carefully for expected calculations. 5. Check for existing formulas — don't overwrite. 6. Note template-specific conventions." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_1a3f6108 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any calculated cell in an LBO model" ;
    oc:directiveContent "NEVER compute values in Python and hardcode results into cells. Always write Excel formula strings (e.g., cell.value = '=B5*B6') so the model remains dynamic." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Hardcoded values break the model's dynamic nature — changing an input won't cascade through calculations, making the model unreliable for scenario analysis." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_433b53d1 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:directiveContent "Python with openpyxl must be available for standalone .xlsx generation; Office JS runtime for live Excel add-in mode. recalc.py at /mnt/skills/public/xlsx/recalc.py for formula validation." .

oc:kn_559a8c7d a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Writing any calculated cell with openpyxl" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
    oc:directiveContent "cell.value = \"=B5*B6\"  # formula string, NOT cell.value = 1250" .

oc:kn_55dc73cf a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building any multi-section financial model" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never build the entire model end-to-end and present it at once. Complete one section, verify with the user, get sign-off, then proceed to the next section." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Later sections depend on earlier ones; catching a mistake in Sources & Uses after returns are built means rework everywhere." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_61d4b78a a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When formatting any cell in the LBO model" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Formula color convention: Blue=hardcoded inputs, Black=calculations, Purple=same-tab links, Green=cross-tab links. Fill palette: dark blue headers (#1F4E79), light blue columns (#D9E1F2), medium blue outputs (#BDD7EE), grey inputs (#F2F2F2), white formulas." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Consistent color coding allows anyone to instantly distinguish inputs from calculations and trace formula origins — a standard investment banking practice." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_691b7369 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:directiveContent "LBO Model sections: Sources & Uses → Operating Model → Debt Schedule → Returns Analysis (IRR/MOIC) → Sensitivity Tables. Each with color-coded formulas, balanced totals, and verified calculations." ;
    oc:templateVariables "Debt_Schedule",
        "Operating_Model",
        "Returns",
        "Sensitivity",
        "Sources_Uses" .

oc:kn_72ce38c7 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building debt schedules or any interest calculation that feeds back into cash flows" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use Beginning Balance (not average or ending) for interest calculations to break circular references. Pattern: Interest → Cash Flow → Paydown → Ending Balance." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Using ending or average balance for interest creates a circular reference where interest depends on cash flow which depends on interest." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_8db3494a a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Standard LBO model build workflow" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Analyze template structure (map sections, timeline, conventions). 2. Build Sources & Uses → verify balance → user sign-off. 3. Build Operating Model/Projections → verify margins → user sign-off. 4. Build Debt Schedule → verify waterfall → user sign-off. 5. Build Returns (IRR/MOIC) → verify signs → user sign-off. 6. Build Sensitivity Tables → verify center cell → user sign-off. 7. Run recalc.py validation. 8. Final formatting pass." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_9bbdeee0 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building sensitivity/tornado tables for IRR, MOIC, or other outputs" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Sensitivity tables must use ODD dimensions (5×5 or 7×7) with the center cell as the base case. Axis values must be symmetric around the base assumption." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Odd dimensions guarantee a true center cell that equals the model's actual output, proving the table is wired correctly." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a34460a1 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SecurityImplication ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building debt paydown or cash sweep formulas" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Debt paydown formulas must use MAX(0, ...) or MIN functions to prevent negative balances. Balances cannot go below zero." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Negative debt balances are meaningless and indicate the model is paying down more debt than exists, which cascades into incorrect interest and return calculations." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a48dc355 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before beginning any LBO model population" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before writing any formula: examine template structure, identify all sections, understand the timeline, note existing formulas, confirm template-specific conventions, and ask the user about any ambiguities." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_bd3b5768 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When a user attaches or provides an LBO template file" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never build from scratch when a template file is provided. Always copy and adapt the provided template." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Templates encode institutional conventions and structure; building from scratch risks inconsistency with expectations and loses pre-built formatting." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_eb2a15cc a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After completing the full LBO model" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Run recalc.py to validate formulas (must return zero errors). Verify sections balance, roll-forwards tie, IRR signs correct, sensitivity center cell matches model output, no #REF!/#DIV/0! errors." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

